1. Overview & Proposed Solution
We propose a Hardened MAVLink 2.0 Proxy that sits between the Ground Control Station (GCS) and the Drone. It acts as a secure tunnel, encapsulating standard MAVLink telemetry and command packets inside a cryptographically secure AEAD (Authenticated Encryption with Associated Data) wrapper.

Standard drone communication protocols (like raw MAVLink) broadcast data in plaintext over radio frequencies, making them highly vulnerable. This solution utilizes the ChaCha20-Poly1305 cipher suite to secure the primary data stream, while utilizing HMAC-SHA256 strictly as a secondary, time-stamped authorization token for high-risk commands (like ARMing the drone).
